FOUR! Shortish one outside off, chance to throw the bat at it for Chase who looks to cut but the ball flies off his outside edge over the slip and gully region. Lucky boundary that one. 100 up for Windies with that boundary.
Bouncer on middle, Chase ducks under it.
Good length ball coming into the batter, blocked off his back foot.
Another bumper! But this is too high for Chase to do anything on that. Ducks under it.

Nice shot! Shortish ball outside off this time from Bumrah. Chase works it nicely through the point and gully region. Jadeja chases the ball and stops it before it touches the fence. Three runs taken.
OUCH! That would've hurt. Loopy ball on shortish length, Hope looks to flick this off his back foot but hits the short leg fielder closer to the neck. Agarwal looks in pain.
Loopy ball outside off, Chase looks to push this towards the off side but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Blocks well to this loopy one by coming forward.
Sharp turn on that one. Shortish length on off and middle, Chase looks to cut but is beaten.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller one down the leg side, Chase looks to work it down the leg side but gets hit on the pad.
Good length ball around the off stump channel, blocked well.
Outswinger outside off, Hope looks to fend at it but the away movement meant that he couldn't get any willow on that one.
Shorter one on the body of Hope who works it off his back foot towards square leg to get a run.
Slightly shortish in length again, Chase works it nicely towards mid on to get off strike.
Bumper outside off, Hope does well to sway away from it.
Fuller one this time, aiming the timbers. Hope gets his bat down in time to block this one out.
Shortish outside off, cut away through point and cover to take a single.
OHH! Flighted and quicker on off and middle, Hope is beaten and the ball goes between bat and pad. Just a bit high or else it would've hit the stumps. Pant fails to collect that one cleanly.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fullish on off, pushed straight to cover.
Loopy and fuller, worked towards mid off.
Gets forward to this one to block it well. Tidy over from Jadeja.
Starts with a fullish one on off, Chase pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, Chase pushes this off his back foot towards short cover.
Good length ball on the stumps, blocked nicely again by Chase.
Back of a length outside off, Chase dabs it towards cover to change ends.
Fuller one around off, blocked nicely again.
Bumper around off to finish the over. Chase ducks under it.
FOUR! Lucky there maybe. Shortish ball on off and middle, Chase goes back and pulls it nicely for a boundary. It was not too far away from the mid-wicket fielder.
Worked on the off side off his back foot, takes a single.
On the middle stump this time, blocked well.
Fuller one from Jadeja, Hope pushes this to mid off.
Fuller down the leg side, worked fine by Hope for a single.
Shortish one outside off, Chase works it through covers to take a single.
Good length ball outside off, Chase leaves it alone.
Good line and length there from Shami. Chase covered his stumps and allowed this one to go the keeper.
Shortish one outside off, Chase punched it off his back foot through point to take a single.
Shorter ball this time. Hope ducks under and lets the keeper collect that one.
FOUR! Creamed through the covers. Full ball from Shami to which Hope leans forward and drives it beautifully through mid off. The fielder there gives it a chase but no chance for him.
Good ball to end the over. Lets this one to come into the body of Hope who blocks it well towards leg side.

Poor effort from the deep cover fielder there. Loopy ball outside off, Chase pushes this through point. The fielder in the deep is lazy to go down quickly which allows Hope to return for the second run.
Fuller one to Chase who works it towards mid off to take a run.
Played off his front foot to this loopy ball around off.
Shorter one this time. Hope goes back to cut it through gully and point. Takes another couple of runs.
Flatter and quicker this time, blocked off his front foot.
Fullish one pushed towards the cover fielder.
Starts with a shortish one on off, pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR! Nicely timed! Wide outside off from Shami on a fullish length. Hope times it superbly through covers. Jadeja gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. If Jadeja can't get to the ball, one should know that the timing is superb on that one.
Blocked this good length ball by getting right behind the delivery.

That sneaked in! Beautiful ball from Shami. Good line and length from Shami, the ball comes in from a good length ball to cut the batsman into half. The ball goes between bat and pad to Pant who can't gather it cleanly as it came to him on the bounce. Looked in pain but is ready to go.
Fullish one this time, pushed firmly towards the bowler.
length ball on middle, Chase looks to cut but gets an inside edge and the ball goes fine down the leg side. Single taken.
Starts his new spell with a good length ball outside off, blocked nicely by Chase.

OUT! Caught! Sharp catch that by KL Rahul! Chase departs just two short of his half century. Oh wait! The umpires are checking for the no ball there. That looks very close. Well, legal one confirms the umpire and Chase takes the long walk back to the pavilion. This is a good length ball on middle, Chase flicks it off his back foot but KL Rahul at square leg takes a sharp catch. End of a 42-run stand. Timely wicket for India this one.
Bumper on the body to welcome the new man, Hetmyer, who hops in his crease to work it towards square leg to get off the mark.
Good length ball on the stumps, Hope does well to block.
Slightly fullish one and closer to the off pole, Hope lunges forward to block.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Hope.
Fullish ball around the fourth stump line, Hetmyer comes forward and times it through covers to take a couple.
Beaten! Shortish length which comes back in. Hetmyer looks to punch this off his back foot but is beaten. Lucky not to edge.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards the off side off his back foot.
Back of a length on the body of Hetmyer who swivels and pulls this towards square leg. Jadeja hares at the ball and flicks it back before it touches the rope. Saved two there
Back of a length ball on off, Hetmyer gets behind the ball to block it on the off side.
Shortish ball around off, Hetmyer looks to work it towards gully but is early into his shot. The ball takes a leading edge and goes towards cover. Hetmyer gets a run.
On a good length on off, Hetmyer pushes it to point.
Bowls a full length down the leg side, Shimron attempts to flick but misses it completely.
Good length ball on off and middle, blocked nicely with soft hands.
Another good length ball coming into the the batter, Hetmyer lunges to block.
Goes past the outside edge this time! Superb ball around the fifth stump line on a good length. Hetmyer has a poke but the ball goes past his hanging bat straight to the keeper.
Fuller on the pads, Hetmyer works it nicely towards mid-wicket to get a single. They wanted a couple there but Jadeja was quick to the ball and they decided against the second run.
Starts with a fuller one on middle, Hetmyer blocks it by coming forward.
Edge but short! Fullish length ball on off, Hetmyer looks to drive this one but gets an outside edge but the ball goes off the outside edge towards KL Rahul at second slip.

FOUR! Another outside edge but this one looked deliberate. Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer dabs it towards the third slip fielder. The ball falls just short of him and he fails to collect and the ball goes for a boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller one this time, Hetmyer pushes it towards cover. This was in the air again but just short. Living dangerously is Hetmyer.
Short ball on the body, pulls it towards square leg to take a run.
Start with a loopy fuller ball, defended towards cover.
Loopy down the leg side, Hetmyer works it fine down the leg side to take a couple. The fielder was slow there allowing the second.
Good length on off, blocked off his front foot.
Fuller and flighted, Shimron pushes this back to the bowler this time.
Fuller one again. Hetmyer Looks to go over the mid on fielder but gets it off his bottom half of the bat towards long on. A run taken.
Hope Blocks this by getting right behind of the line of the delivery.
Length ball on the pads, worked towards the leg side to take a run.
Shorter around off this time, Hope guides it through gully and takes a couple. Ishant chases the ball and sends it back to the keeper.

Timing on that one was superb! Fullish ball outside off, Hope gets into position and plays a perfect cover drive. The ball was racing towards the fence but Agarwal chases  it and save a run as the batters take three.
Goes for a yorker this time. Hetmyer gets his bat in time to block. The ball rolls towards mid-wicket and the batters take one.
Wow! Another solid timing from Hope. A straight one on a fullish length from Bumrah. Hope gets in the perfect position again and pushes this past the bowler sweetly to pick up another brace.
Wide outside off, left alone this time.
Loopy delivery on off, Hetmyer defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Flighted delivery on off, Hetmyer comes down the track and lofts this over between the mid off and cover fielder for a boundary.
Looped up ball on middle, Hetmyer blocks it out.
Shorter delivery on middle, Shimron flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Hope plays it to cover.
Flighted delivery on middle, Hope flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Starts with a loopy shortish one, Hope pushes it past the bowler who dives to his right to stop but fails to do so. They take a run as the ball goes towards mid on.
What a stop that from Jadeja! Short ball outside off, Hetmyer crunches this towards point but can't get past Jadeja. He has been a live wire on the ground.
Full toss on off, Hetmyer pushes this through mid off to take a run.
Loopy ball around off, turns away from the right-hander who looks to play at it but decided against it at the last moment.
Loopy ball on off and middle, worked straight to mid on.
Shortish ball outside off, Hope wanted to heave this down the leg side but pushed awkwardly straight to mid off.
Fullish one on middle, tucked straight to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball outside off, worked towards cover to change ends.
Flighted ball on middle, worked towards mid off and take a quick run.
Fullish one which is pushed back to the bowler.
Too straight and flighted one, pushed confidently towards mid on. Hetmyer takes a run.
Another full ball tapped right of the bowler. They take a single.
Loopy one Outside off, left alone.
Shortish one outside off, Hope cuts it through point to pick up a single.

Nearly a wicket for Vihari! Quicker ball to which Hetmyer looks to push but gets an inside edge which sneaks between bat and pad. Ishant chases it down to the third man to save a boundary. Three taken there.
Wide outside off, asking for a drive but left alone.
Outside off, comes across to block this one.
Shortish ball on middle, pulled through square leg for a run.
Fuller one, pushed back to the bowler.
Another fullish ball, pushed towards mid on, Jadeja looks to stop but misses. They take a run.
Full ball down the leg side, flicked down the fine leg by Hetmyer to take a run.
Loopy fullish one this time, pushed back to Jadeja
This time outside off, Hope comes forward to dab it towards the leg side but dabs it off the inside edge closer to the short leg fielder.
This time he defends it solidly.
Good length ball down the leg side, Hetmyer looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball closer to the off stump, Hetmyer lunges forward to block.
Shortish one this time, closer to the body again but Hetmyer is right behind the line to block it well again.
Goes round the wicket and looks to bowl a shortish one on the body. It goes down the leg side with the angle but Hetmyer manages to pull nicely to pick up a single.
Wide outside off this time, Hope lets it be.

OUT! Caught by Pant coming forward. Yes, a clean catch that one. Fullish length ball outside off, shapes a tad bit away as Hope has a poke. Gets an outside edge and the ball goes to the keeper. It dips as it goes to Pant who comes forward to pouch this one comfortably. Some doubts there regarding the catch but Hope has to walk back as it looks a clean catch and the same has been confirmed by the third umpire. Another timely wicket for India and another Windies batter walks back after getting a decent start.Ishant gets his third. West Indies still behind by 123 runs.
Good length ball on the body, worked towards mid on for nothing.
Slightly fuller this time around off, guided through the gully region for a single.
Good length ball which is coming into the batter, Holder covers his off stump and lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish ball on middle and off, Holder pushes this straight to mid on.
Wide outside off this time, Holder leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter in length, closer to the fifth stump line. Holder lets it go to the keeper again.
FOUR! Shortish length outside off from Ishant, Hetmyer guides it nicely through the gully region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer looks to guide it again in the same direction but he is beaten this time.

OUT! Superb catch of his own bowling by Ishant. They again check for the front foot no ball but this is safe. Good length ball on middle and leg, Hetmyer looks to push with hard hands towards mid on but because of the closed bat face, the ball lobs towards Ishant. He does really well to get down and grab that one nicely. Number four for Ishant as he removes another set Windies batsman. It is just his third caught and bowled in 91 Test matches. Can he take a fifer here?
Good length ball outside off, Roach blocks it off his back foot.
Good length ball on stumps this time, blocked again.

OUT! CAUGHT! Fifer for Ishant as Kohli gobbles this catch in the second slip. West Indies in all sorts of trouble now. Fullish ball around the fifth stump, Roach looks to drive this one but the ball takes an outside edge and goes straight to Kohli at second slip. The skipper is not going to miss out on that one. He takes it comfortably and celebrates with his bowler. 9th fifer for Ishant and this one has left Windies reeling. The hosts are still trailing by 118 runs.
Good length ball on off, blocked by Holder.
Full ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler by Holder.
Fuller again outside off, Holder times it straight to mid off.
FOUR! Fuller length outside off from Shami. Holder opens the face of the bat and guides this through the vacant third man region to get off the mark with a boundary.
Fullish ball on the pads, Holder flicks it nicely through mid-wicket. They take three before the ball is back to the keeper.
Shortish length on the hips, worked down the leg side for nothing.
Goes past the outside edge of the opposition skipper with a beauty. Pitched on a good length closer to the off pole. Holder has a poke at it but misses to put bat on ball.
Fuller this time as Holder flicks it nicely towards square leg. He denies the single there.

In the air but safe! Good length ball on middle this time, Holder looks to heave this towards mid wicket but the ball takes the leading edge and lobs high in the air. Vihari runs from third man and makes a diving effort but can't reach the ball. Ishant Sharma is not a happy man because of that effort there.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.
Another leading edge as Holder looks to flick this fullish ball towards the leg side. The ball goes to the cover fielder and Holder takes a run. He is farming the strike here.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, rises slightly on the hips, Holder works it fine down the leg side but denies a run.
Good length outside off, Holder covers his off pole and lets it go to Pant.
Goes for a slower on this time but it is again wide on the off side, leaves it alone.
Fullish around off, Holder lunges forward to block it back to the bowler.
Good length around off again, blocked towards gully by Holder with a solid push.
Slower one this time but closer to off pole, blocked nicely by Holder. And, that's STUMPS on Day 2.
Starts with a good length delivery on middle, Cummins attempts to defend but misses and gets hit on the box. He looks in serious pain here and is lying down on the ground.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Bowls it full on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but misses it completely.
Another full delivery outside off, Cummins looks to defend but changes his mind and lets it go in the end.
Good length delivery on middle, Cummins defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Cummins blocks it out.
Good length ball on off, Holder defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Holder drives this nicely towards mid on. No run.
Good length delivery on off, Holder drives this towards cover and takes a brace. Mayank Agarwal runs after the ball and cleans it up.
On a length outside off, Holder guides it to third man and takes a single. Cummins has two balls to survive.
Bumrah loses his line here. It is a full delivery way down the leg side, Miguel looks to flick but misses.
Good length delivery on off, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Good ball from Ishant. It is a good length ball on the fourth stump line, Holder looks to defend but misses. Lucky not to have edged that ball as it just passed the bat by a whisker.
Good length ball on middle, Holder flicks it to fine leg but refuses to take a single.

Good length ball on off, Holder looks to defend but gets an outside edge which bounces just in front of Pant. It is another good delivery from Ishant which induces this edge from Holder who plays this with soft hands. The keeper makes a good diving stop on the bounce behind the stumps.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Holder pushes this to cover-point and takes a single.
BOUNCER! It is aimed at the body, Cummins does well to duck under it.
On a good length outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.

Good length ball wide outside off, Holder looks to push it through covers but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball rolls towards third man. There was a run on offer but Holder will keep as much of the strike as he can and that's why he does not take a run.
Fuller on middle and leg, Holder pushes it towards mid on.
Good length ball on off, Holder pushes this to cover.
Another fuller one outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder again.
FOUR! First boundary of the day for the hosts. Full and around off, Holder just opens the face of the bat and guides it between point and gully towards the third man fence.
Wide! Way wide outside the off stump and Holder does not fiddle with it. Wide signaled by the umpire.

FOUR! 200 up for the hosts. This is almost identical to the last boundary. Full and outside off, Jason opens the face of the bat and guides this to the point fence. Cummins now will have to face the first ball of the next over as Holder fails to retain the strike. A very rare expensive over by Bumrah, 9 runs off it.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Cummins lets it go to the keeper.
Bowls a full delivery coming around the wicket outside the off pole line, Cummins is happy to leave it alone.
BEATEN! Good ball from Sharma, bowls this on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but is unable to put bat on it. Ishant should look to bowl more on this channel.
Another play and miss! It is a full delivery on the fourth stump line, Cummins again goes for a defense but misses it again.

Third play and a miss from Cummins! Excellent over comes to an end from Ishant. It is another full delivery outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but gets beaten again. It misses the bat by a whisker.
On a good length on middle, Holder blocks it out.
Full delivery on off, Holder pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Jason plays this towards mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played from Holder. It is a back of a length delivery on off, Holder rocks back and lofts this over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
NO BALL! It is a low full toss on off, Holder flicks it but does not time it well. It goes past the mid on fielder and they take a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Holder goes for a defense but gets an outside edge which bounces in front of first slip.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Holder pushes this to the leg side off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Very full delivery outside the off stump line, Cummins leaves it alone.
BOUNCER! A good one at that. It is aimed at the body and Cummins ducks under it.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but misses.
Another play and a miss! It is another full delivery on the fourth stump line. Cummins looks to defend but fails to put bat on it. It is fifth play and a miss in the span of three overs.
Very full delivery outside the off pole line, Cummins this time leaves it alone.
Full delivery on the pads, Holder flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Cummins goes for the defense but misses.
Another play and a miss! Loopy delivery on off, Cummins goes for another defense and misses the ball.
Flatter delivery ooutside off, Cummins attempts to defend again but is unable to put bat on it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Cummins finally puts bat on it and defends it to cover.
BEATEN! Another flighted ball outside off, Cummins right now is unable to put bat on it. Miguel goes for a defense again but misses.
Full on middle and leg, Holder flicks it to deep fine leg but does not take the single as he wants to keep the strike.

NOT OUT! However, the review has been retained by India. The umpire signaled not out but the ball is clipping the top of middle and leg. This one is pitched on a good length around off, the ball nips back in with the angle and hits Holder on the back pad and carries to Pant after that. Jason is on the front foot and maybe it's his big stature that the umpire takes into account as the Indian players are denied after a loud appeal. After a bit of consideration with Shami, Kohli goes for the review. Ultra Edge comes in and shows no bat involved. Now comes the Ball Tracker, pitched outside off, impact in line, clipping the top of middle and leg. Umpire's call and Holder survives. India though retain the review.
Again beaten! Outside off, length ball, Holder looks to defend but does so inside the line.
Fuller this time, pushed towards mid on by Jason.
Length delivery just outside off nipping back in, Holder misses his pull and is hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Boundary to end the first over of Shami today. Length ball outside off, Holder pulls this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flatter delivery outside the off pole line, Cummins leaves it alone.
Looped up ball on middle, Cummins blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Cummins defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Another one from Cummins. Jadeja comes around the wicket and pushes this ball outside off, Cummins goes for a defense but misses.
Another play and a miss! Cummins attempts to defend this flighted delivery outside off but misses the ball completely.

Third play and a miss in a row! Cummins has faced 35 balls in this innings and is yet to get off the mark. It is a flighted delivery on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but misses the ball again. He has played and missed a lot of ball in this innings so far and should consider himself lucky to not edge any of that.
Fuller one around off, pushed towards cover by Holder.
Beaten! Holder living dangerously here. Length ball around off pole, it pitches and moves away. Holder hangs his bat at it but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Some pondering by Holder but he trusts Cummins this time and takes a single. Length ball around off, Jason guides it towards the empty point region and takes a single.
Outside off, Cummins lets this one through to Pant. Wasteful ball by Shami.
Another length ball outside off, Cummins looks to block this one out but bails out in the end.
This time Shami attacks the stumps, Cummins blocks it out well off the back foot.
Flighter delivery on off, Holder pushes this towards cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Holder blocks it out.
Fullish delivery on middle, Holder flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple to keep the strike.
Floated delivery on middle, Jason defends it to short leg.
Looped up ball on middle, Jason pushes this to mid on and gives Cummins to face the last ball of the over.
Loopy delivery on middle, Cummins defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Holder flicks it to mid-wicket.
Another full delivery on middle, Holder pushes this to short mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middel, Holder defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on the off stump line, Holder pushes this to cover-point and takes a single.

NOT OUT! It is a full delivery outside the off stump line, Cummins goes for a defense but misses. Shami and the keeper goes for an appeal and the umpire gives it out. Cummins goes for the review straight away indicating that it has not hit the bat. The replays roll in, the front foot is fine and Ultra Edge shows that there is a distance between the bat and ball. Cummins survives. He has faced 40 deliveries and is yet to get off the mark.
Bouncer! It is bowled on the leg stump line, Cummins does well to duck under it.
Flat outside the off pole, blocked out by Jason.
This time slower through the air, again defended by Holder.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards the off side.
Holder takes a single and gives the strike to Cummins to negotiate the last 2 balls of this over. Full and pushed towards mid on as Holder crosses end.
Cummins is beaten at this one. Flatter trajectory and going away from Cummins with the angle, he looks to defend but misses.
Again similar delivery, Cummins is beaten again.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Excellent delivery from Shami. It is a good length ball outside the off stump line, Holder goes for a drive but gets a thick outside edge back to the keeper. The Windies seriously needed Holder to stay out there in the middle in order to get any closer to India's score. A good partnership of 41 runs comes to an end. The hosts still trail by 77 runs.

NOT OUT! BIG SHOUT FOR LBW! Shami bowls a full delivery on the leg stump, Gabriel goes for a flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shami goes for a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Shami and co. go for a review but it looks desperate. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the impact was outside leg stump. Poor review from India and they have lost their first review.
Good length delivery on off, Gabriel plays it to mid off.
BEATEN! It is a good length ball outside off, Gabriel looks to drive but misses the ball completely.
Full delivery on middle, Gabriel flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a good length outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but fails to put ball on it.
Jadeja around the wicket, bowls this one flatter and on middle and leg, it hits the inside half of Gabriel's bat and the ball rolls towards fine leg for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! The Windies have been bowled out for 222 and trail India by 75 runs going into the third innings. Cummins is the last man to be dismissed after he faced 45 balls without scoring a single run! Jadeja comes around the wicket and bowls this one flatter and on the off pole, it spins back in just towards Cummins. He goes to slog sweep it but misses the ball altogether and it crashes into the off pole. The stumps are shattered and after a frustrating opening hour for the visitors, they have taken both the wickets quickly after Drinks.
Roach starts the third innings with a short of a length ball outside off,  KL Rahul pushes this towards the point region.
Again outside off by Kemar Roach, Rahul guides it to the fielder at point off the back foot.
This time a better line by Kemar but Rahul knows exactly where his stumps are. He shuffles across and lets the ball through to Shai Hope.
India are underway! Fuller this time on middle and leg, Rahul pushes this one through mid-wicket for a couple.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Fullish one on off, pushed back by Rahul towards the off side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Falls short of first slip!  First ball for Agarwal and he was a goner if Darren Bravo at first slip was a bit ahead. Length ball around off, it was a jaffa from Gabriel first up to Mayank. He tries to block it out but gets an outside edge on it which falls short of first slip. Maybe it was a catch for Shai Hope as he might have had a better chance reaching that one. The ball is missed by both, Darren Bravo and Shai Hope and it races towards the third man fence for a boundary.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball just outside off, Agarwal pushes this through the point region and takes a couple.
Another length ball, this time on the body and Agarwal blocks it out towards the bowler.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball on off,  Agarwal negotiates this one as he blocks this one out too.
Fullish around off, pushed to mid off by KL.
On the pads of Rahul this time, he flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a couple.
Fuller and attacking the stumps here Roach, Rahul pushes it back towards the off side.
Again fuller and on off, pushed to the off side.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Beaten off the last ball. Good length ball just outside off, Rahul looks to push at it but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Fullish around off, pushed towards mid off by Mayank.
Full on middle and leg, Mayank pushes this ball towards the fielder at mid on.
Outside off, good length ball, pushed to the fielder at cover.
Bouncer on the off pole line, Agarwal does well to sway away from it.
Quick single this time by Mayank to end the over. Good length ball around middle and leg, he flicks it wide of mid on and takes a quick single. Good athleticism from the Indian batters.
Full on off and middle, MA pushes it back towards mid on.
Outside off and full by Kemar, Mayank opens the face of the bat and guides this to the man at point. He was thinking about the run but is sent back by KL.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards cover.

Another quick single by Agarwal. He pushes this full ball towards mid off and sets off for a quick run. The man there runs a bit to his left, gathers the ball and has shy at the bowler's end. He misses and Agarwal is home. However, even if he did hit, Agarwal was well inside.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman towards the leg side.
Fuller again on middle and off, pushed to the fielder at cover.
Floated on the pads of Agarwal, he blocks it towards the leg side.
Full and tossed up on off, blocked out.
Again on the pads, Agarwal pushes this towards mid on.
Chase floats this one again on the pads, blocked towards short leg.
Down the leg side this time by Chase, Agarwal lets it be.
Another fuller delivery and around off, pushed back to Chase.
On the pads of Rahul by Holder, he looks to flick this one but misses.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Outside off, length ball, Rahul does not fiddle with it.
On the pads of Rahul, he flicks it towards mid on.
Another one, short of a length, defended off the back foot by Rahul.
On the pads of KL again, he flicks this through mid-wicket. Roach chases it and cuts it off before the ball reaches the ropes and meanwhile the batters take two. LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Flatter on the pads to start off the second session. Agarwal blocks it out.
FOUR! Another one full and down the leg side. Agarwal goes down on one knee and paddle sweeps it fine towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the leg side again, Agarwal blocks it out towards short leg.
Agarwal presents the full face of the bat and blocks this floated one back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Agarwal lets that one be. Some turn and bounce on that delivery as it carries to the keeper.
Down the leg side and Rahul tries to flick it but it misses everything. Shai Hope does well to dive to his left and get a hand to it.
Good length ball on the off pole, Rahul defends it out.
On the pads of KL, he defends it towards mid on.
Again on the leg pole line, Rahul flicks it towards deep fine leg and takes a single.
Fuller and on the pads, Agarwal flicks this in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket. The fielders chase and mop up as the batters take a couple.
Down the leg side, left alone by Mayank.
Length ball outside off, pushed back off the back foot.
Rahul blocks this one out towards short leg off his pads.
Rahul comes down the track to this floated ball around off and blocks it out.
Again shortish and around off, Rahul defends it towards the off side.
Good length and flat on the pads, Rahul flicks it towards backward square leg for a single.
Last ball of the over, floated around off. Rahul comes down the track and blocks it out.
Beaten! Agarwal needs to stabilise here. Length ball around the off pole, it pitches and straightens. Agarwal hangs his bat out but misses the ball by a whisker. Lucky for him.
Length ball on middle and off, defended towards the bowler.

Agarwal gets some bat on this one and survives because if he had missed that he was plumb LBW. Fullish around off, it comes back in with the angle into Agarwal. He looks to flick but just manages an inside edge on it and the ball goes on to hit his pads then.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a couple.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on the off pole, Agarwal defends it out.
Rahul comes down the track and pushes this towards mid on for a single.
Floated on the pads of Agarwal, he blocks it out.
Short and flatter this time by Chase. He gets some turn and bounce on this one as the ball turns into Agarwal. He manages to go on the back foot and defend it towards point.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal defends it towards the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, short one. Agarwal leaves this one alone.
FOUR! Lead above 100 runs for India with this shot. Shorter and outside off, Rahul goes onto the back foot and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on the body, Rahul blocks it out.
On the hips of Rahul, he pulls this one towards deep square leg for a couple by getting on his toes.
Length ball outside off, Rahul gets the under half of his bat onto this one and the ball bounces onto the pitch.
Outside off, Rahul leaves this one alone.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated outside off, Agarwal blocks this one off the back foot.

OUT! LBW! Mayank Agarwal is out of here and departs cheaply in consecutive innings. Chase floats this one full and just around the off pole, Mayank looks to paddle sweep this one but misses the ball completely to get hit on the front leg. It looks plumb to the naked eye. After consulting with Rahul at the non-striker's end, Agarwal decides against taking the review. But wait, replays roll in, Hawk Eye comes into play and it shows that the ball was MISSING LEG. Mayank would be feeling unlucky here but on the first instance it looked to be crashing into the stumps. India lose their first wicket with 30 runs on the board.
Full and floated on the pads, Pujara pushes this towards mid on and gets off the mark with a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Again tossed up on middle and leg, this time Rahul drives this towards mid on and takes a single.
Pujara blocks this one out by getting onto the front foot and reaching the pitch of the ball.
Length ball just outside off, Rahul blocks this one towards the off side.
Outside off and left alone by Rahul.
Full and on the off side, Rahul defends it towards mid off.
Another ball outside off which is left alone by Rahul.
Good length ball around off, Rahul initially looks to leave it but plays at this one at the last moment as he guides this one towards point. Single taken and Holder looks disappointed.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shortish and flatter by Chase, Rahul defends it off the back foot. There seems to be some turn on the pitch now.
Rahul dances down the wicket and pushes this one towards mid on for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pujara comes down the track to flick it o the leg side but gets a leading edge back towards the bowler.
This looks to be the plan against Roston Chase. Come down the track and negate the spin. And that is what Pujara is doing here.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Again down the track and Pujara pushes it back to Chase.

Rahul pulls this short ball but hasn't timed it well. It skies towards backward square leg but falls short of the fielder who is running in towards the ball. Maybe a better effort from him and Rahul would have been walking back into the pavilion.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Another one outside off and Pujara lets it go to Shai Hope.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Pujara attempts to fend at it but gets hit on the gloves towards the leg side.
On the pads of Pujara, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Pujara comes down the track and pushes this towards mid-wicket to take a single.
Outside off, floated on a good length, Rahul pads it out.
Down the leg side but this time Rahul offers no shot to this one as it hits his pad.
Shorter this time on off, Chase punches this one off the back foot towards the bowler.
Looped up ball on off, Rahul blocks it out to point.
On the pads, full and floated. Rahul blocks this one out towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Pujara leaves it alone this time.
Yorker this time coming in with the angle by Holder, Pujara flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes one.
Length ball outside off, pushed to point by Rahul.
Full and on the off pole, Rahul blocks it out towards the cover fielder.
Another fuller one outside off, Rahul blocks it out towards the off side.
What was that? A very unorthodox pull by Rahul to this short ball down the leg side as he just dabs it off the back foot towards the leg side for one.
Good length ball floated outside off, Rahul looks to pad it out but just gets a hint of the pad on it.
Fuller one and on the pads, Rahul pushes this one down the ground towards mid on and takes a single.
Pujara dances down the track and does well to block this good length delivery.
Pujara is hit on the pads off this flatter one outside off.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara rocks onto the back foot and cuts this through covers for a double.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Beaten! Jaffa by Gabriel to start off his second spell. Pitching it on a good length around off, it swings away. Rahul looks to defend but does so inside the line and is beaten.
A great ball followed up by a bad ball which releases all the pressure. On the pads of Rahul, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Yorker this time and Rahul does well to jam it out towards mid on.

FOUR! Shot of the day! Full and on the off pole, Rahul leans into this one and just drives it straight back past the bowler towards mid off for a boundary. Gabriel tries to bend to his right and save it but no luck here for him.
Defended off the back foot by Rahul towards square leg.
Full on middle and off, Rahul blocks it out presenting the full face of the bat.
Rahul looks to pad this full and floated one outside off but misses.
Tossed up on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Good late cut by Rahul and he moves to 30 with this shot. Short and wide outside off, Rahul rocks onto the back foot and cuts it between point and gully towards the third man fence. Holder chases after it but fails to pull it back in time.
This time Rahul pushes this floated one on middle and leg towards mid on and takes one.
Short and wide by Chase this time, Pujara cuts it through covers and takes a couple.
Floated on the pads of Pujara, he knocks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Shorter delivery on off, Pujara rocks back and plays it to point.
Shorter in length on middle, Pujara pulls it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Another short delivery on off, Rahul cuts it to cover and crosses over for a single.
Short ball on off, Pujara cuts it to third man and takes a couple.
Flighted delivery on middle, Cheteshwar comes down the track and pads it away.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket. Four runs from Campbell's first over.
Full and on the pads of Rahul, he flicks it towards deep fine leg for a single.
Full and on the pads again, Pujara blocks this one out towards mid on.
Full and on the off side, pushed towards the mid off fielder.
Full toss outside off, Pujara pushes this one towards the gap in the cover region. The fielders mop it up in the deep and the batters take three in the meantime.
On the pads of Rahul, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and flat outside off, pushed to the fielder at point.
Floated on middle and off, pushed back towards Roston.
On the pads of Rahul, he tucks it to the fielder at short leg.
Again on the pads, blocked out by Rahul.
Full and floated around off, pushed back towards mid off.
Another one tossed up on off, driven back to Roston.
Full and on the off pole, Pujara pushes it back towards Shannon.
Length ball this time on middle and leg, Pujara pushes this one towards mid on.
Fuller on middle and leg, Pujara drives it back to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara pushes this one out.
Good length ball on middle, Cheteshwar pushes this one towards Gabriel.
Yorker length outside off, Pujara opens the face of his bat and guides this one towards the point region. The fielder there dives to his left and makes a very good stop.
Kemar Roach with his first ball of the new spell and bowls it outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.

Missed by a whisker! Roach bowls this one on a length and gets it to move away after pitching. Rahul goes to play at it and almost gets an edge on it. The Windies players appeal loudly but it seems out of desperation more than anything else.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball just outside off, pushed toward the point region by Rahul.
Outside off, left alone by Rahul at the last possible moment.
Another one outside off, Rahul pushes this one towards the cover fielder.
Comes down the track and Pujara blocks it out.
Floated on middle and leg, this time pushes this one towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Pujara comes down the track and pushes this through the gap at cover. The fielder hares after it and mops up as the batters take two.
This time tossed up on leg, pushed towards mid-wicket for a single.
On the pads of the batsman, works it down the leg side.
Fuller one on middle and off, Rahul blocks this one back towards the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Cheteshwar.
Fuller and attacking the stumps, this one is pushed towards mid on.
Outside off again, left alone by the defensive maestro Pujara.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara again.
Length ball on the body, pushed back towards the bowler.
Good length ball on the wickets, pushed back by Pujara.
FOUR! The sluggish outfield has reduced the amount of boundaries but this one does go to the fence. Wide and outside off, pushed towards the fence at point for a boundary.

OUT! BOWLED! What was that from Rahul? A total lapse of concentration maybe. Chase floats this one outside off, and it turns towards the wicket. Rahul goes down on one knee and tries to play the paddle sweep but completely misses the ball and it shatters into the stumps. He was way too early into the shot and is deceived by the slowness of the delivery. Rahul departs after getting off to another fine start. India are effectively 148/2 and still hold the advantage over the hosts.
Shortish outside off, Kohli opens the face of the bat and guides it towards third man for a couple. The skipper is off the mark with that.
Kohli has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Chase floats this one around off and Kohli blocks this one out.
Full and floated on middle and off, pushed back straight towards the bowler. End of a successful over for the West Indies.
FOUR! Good shot from Pujara. It is a short ball outside off, Pujara rocks back and slaps it past the cover and point fielder for a boundary. Good start to the over.
Another short delivery outside off, Pujara again slaps it past cover but this time the fielder chases this down. Pujara wants three but is sent back by Virat Kohli. There was no run there.

OUT! BOWLED! Beautiful delivery from Roach. It is bowled on a good length outside off which swung into the batsman. Pujara looks to defend but the ball goes between the bat and pad and it goes on to hit the stumps. Pujara's defense has been breached which is rarity for him. Roach comes back well after being hit for a boundary on the first ball. Back-to-back wickets for Windies. They have a chance to peg India back here.

Good bouncer to end the session. Holder hits the deck hard with this one and on the off pole line. Kohli does well to sway away from it and it is TEA ON DAY 3!
Short delivery on middle, Rahane pushes it to mid on.

Kemar convinces the captain to take the review which seems more of a desperation. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball was missing the leg stump. West Indies lose one of their two reviews.

DROPPED! Campbell is the culprit. It is a good length delivery on middle, Rahane looks to flick again but gets a thick outside edge towards cover where Campbell makes a dive forward but is unable to hold onto the catch. Rahane is a big miss as he is playing really well here and he can bat for really long periods. He should make use of this opportunity to make a big score here.

50 up for vice-captain Ajinkya Rahane! He brings it up with this single. Ajinkya pushes this length ball outside off towards the point region for one. A simple celebration as he lifts his bat towards the dressing room. He has rode his luck but he will be happy as he is still out in the middle with his skipper and will be looking for the ton now.

BYES! Loses his line does Gabriel here. It is bowled down the leg side, Kohli looks to flick but misses and ball goes past the keeper for 2 byes. It is STUMPS ON DAY 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! Chase removes skipper Kohli in his very first over of the day. Flighted delivery around off and middle, Kohli looks to work this towards the leg side but he closes the face of the bat early and gets a leading edge. The ball lobs towards Campbell at short cover who takes the ball over his head in the second attempt. Early blow for India. The 106-run stand between Rahane and Kohli is broken. A very soft dismissal for Kohli this, which we do not see very often. Third wicket for Chase in this innings.
Full and floated on the pads. Vihari pushes it back towards Chase.
Another one on the pads, Vihari guides it towards fine leg and takes a single to get off the mark. He retains strike for the next over too.
Fullish ball on the fourth stump line, pushed towards mid off.

This time a loopy ball on middle, comes down the track to push it back to the bowler.
Comes forward to this flatter ball to block it off his front foot.
Rahane works this towards mid on to take a run.
Flatter outside off, Vihari comes out of the crease to blunt this onto the pitch.
Shortish loopy ball on the pads, flicked fine by Vihari to take a couple.
Good length ball on off, comes into Rahane who stays in his crease to block this towards mid-wicket.
Short one on the body, Rahane works it off his back foot towards mid-wicket. Vihari wanted a run there but Rahane is not keen on that.
Good length ball outside off this time, blocked nicely by Rahane .
Good length ball on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket.

The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Comes down the track and pushes this one towards cover.
Another loopy ball outside off, pushed to cover again.

Flatter one on middle, worked towards the leg side to take a run.
Drives towards mid on again to this loopy ball on middle for another run.
Comes forward to block this one.
On the pads this time, tucked fine down the leg side to take a couple.

FOUR BYES! Goes for the sweep this time as Campbell pushes this down the leg side on a fullish length. Vihari can't get his bat on it while Hope can't do anything else either. The ball races fine for a boundary.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, worked nicely through mid on for an easy single.
Flighted on middle this time, worked nicely towards mid-wicket to change ends.
Flat and wide, Rahane guides towards third man to take a run.
Fuller one on middle, worked towards the leg side.
Blocked by lunging forward this time by Vihari to this full ball.
Fuller around off, driven straight to Chase.
Starts with a good length ball around off, blocked towards the leg side.
Good length ball around off again, pushed towards cover this time.
Fullish one on the stumps, Rahane works it towards mid-wicket this time.
Another fullish ball on the stumps, blocked nicely again.
Good length ball in the channel outside off this time. The ball shapes a bit into Rahane. He blocks by lunging forward.
Another ball in the channel outside off, Rahane covers his stumps and lets this go to the keeper.
Overpitched ball around off, Vihari leans forward and drives it superbly between cover and point. Paul chases the ball, slides and saves a couple of runs for his side. Good work from the substitute.

Wide outside off this time, left alone.

FOUR! Superbly timed! Fullish ball on off, crunched through mid off for a boundary. 7 runs from that over.
Fuller and just outside off, pushed towards the fielder at cover.
Fuller again, this time on the pads. Rahane flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a couple.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one is on middle and leg, Rahane looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. The Windies players appeal but nothing from the umpire. Ball Tracker comes in and shows to be missing leg. Good that Holder decided against taking the review.
Fuller one on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, blocked off his front foot.
Fuller again, blocked towards cover.
FOUR! Sweetly timed. Full toss on off, Vihari drives this nicely wide off the mid on fielder to get back-to-back boundaries off Gabriel. The lead goes over 300 with that boundary.
Shortish one around off, blocked off his back foot.
That made a crunching sound. Fuller one again, Vihari punches it nicely to the left of Roach who made a half stop. The ball rolls towards long on and the batters change end.
Shortish ball into the ribs, Rahane works it fine down the leg side to take a couple.
Back of a length around off this time, blocked off his back foot.
Good running that. Shortish one coming into Rahane who tucks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a quick couple.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
Fuller this time, attacking the off pole here Roach. Vihari flicks this exactly towards the man at mid-wicket.
Beaten! In the corridor of uncertainty this one, on the fourth stump line. Vihari looks to block it out but does so inside the line.

Again beaten! Great bowling by Roach. This time on a driving length, Roach lures Vihari into the shot. He looks to push this one towards mid on but gets beaten all ends up.

Beaten for the third time in the over. Roach looks distraught but gets a clap from his captain. Another one just outside off, Vihari looks to block this one out but again is beaten by the away movement on the ball. A menacing over from Roach comes to an end.
Full ball on the pads, Rahane works it nicely towards deep square leg. The fielder down there cuts it off, so just a run.

Bumper on the body! Shortish ball coming into Rahane who hops to work this down the leg side but is hit on the body. Rahane looks in pain as the ball has hit him hard. Gabriel struggling too here as he grimaces after bowling the ball. Goes back to finish the over though.
Shortish around off this time, blocked on the leg side.
Starts with a good length ball around off, blocked nicely.
Fuller ball on off and middle, Vihari blocks it back to the bowler.
