Wide outside off, Rahane guides it off his back foot towards third man but Brooks dives to his right to save runs.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards cover to take a quick run. Hetmyer there has a shy at the stumps but misses.

Poor fielding this time. Good length ball outside off, Vihari directs this through the diving slip fielder with soft hands to take a couple. The fielder gives it a chase and slides to push the ball back in play. Saves a couple.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller one on middle, tucked straight to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on the stumps again, blocked comfortably by Rahane.
Fuller one this time, Rahane looks to work this through mid-wicket but misses his flick and is hit on the pads. A mild appeal from Windies player but it was going down the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, tucked towards the leg side.
Good length ball outside off again, blocked off his front foot.
Starts with a fuller loopy ball, Vihari pushes it back to Chase.
Loopy one again on off and middle, blocked.
Flatter one outside off, left alone.
Fuller one going down the leg side. Vihar looks to sweep but misses.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball on the legs, worked fine for a couple.
Good length ball on off, blocked nicely.
FOUR! Creamed through the covers. Fullish ball outside off, Rahane leans forward and crunches this through covers
Short one around off, tapped towards point.
Shortish one again, pushed towards cover for a run.
Fuller one on the pads, stroked straight to mid on.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Full and floated on middle, Rahane pushes it towards long on and takes one.
Short of a length outside off, Vihari takes one as he cuts it towards backward point.
Short again on the body this time, Rahane pulls it towards square leg.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full and floated on middle, flicked towards mid on for a single.
Vihari blocks out the last ball off his front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball on off, placed towards point for a run.
Bumper but too high. Vihari ducks under it.
Fullish one on the pads, tucked towards fine leg for a run.
Fuller outside off, blocked nicely by Rahane coming forward.
Good length on middle, pushed towards the leg side.
Short one, closer to off stump, worked through covers for a single off his back foot.
Loopy full toss on off, pushed straight to the cover fielder.

Another flighted ball. Rahane dances down the track to convert it into a full toss and slams this through mid-wicket for a boundary. Poor effort from the long on fielder there as he made almost no attempt to stop the ball.
Drives this one towards long on to take a run. Sensible from Rahane.
Blocked coming forward to this flatter ball.
Fuller one and wide. Pushed towards off side.
Loopy one on off and middle, pushed through mid on for a run.
Good length ball on middle and off, Vihari blocks it out back to the bowler.
Length ball outside off, pushed to third man.
Length ball just outside off, defended towards the man at cover-point.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
This time fuller and outside off, Vihari again leaves this one alone.
Wide outside off, left alone by Vihari. Maiden by Holder.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahane comes down the track and pushes this towards mid on for a run. Half stop from the fielder there.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, pushed to mid-wicket.
Fuller one on off, punched straight to mid off.
FOUR! Length ball but going down, pulled nicely by Vihari. The ball goes to the fine leg fence all along the ground.
FOUR! Another boundary. Loopy fullish ball on middle, Vihari crunches it through mid-wicket for another boundary. Top shot that.
Full and floated just outside off, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Bumper to start the over, Vihari ducks under it.
Good length ball on the body, tucked fine down the leg side to take a couple.
Bumper on the body this time, fended towards point this time.
Good length ball coming into the batsman, he pushes this towards cover.
Shortish ball on the pads, looks to place this down the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.

FOUR! Top shot to get to his second half century in Tests. Fuller ball on off, Vihari drives it firmly through mid off. No chance for the fielder there. Also, the lead is 350 now. Nothing going Windies' way at the moment.
Loopy one on off, pushed through mid on for a run.
Full one on the stumps, worked with the turn to change ends.
Blocked towards the leg side.
Comes down the track to this wide ball and blocks.
Shortish one on middle and leg, pushed towards square leg for a run.
Blocked off his front foot this time.
Full on the pads, worked towards mid on, Vihari wanted a run there but is sent back by Rahane.
Good length ball angling in, worked towards square leg with the angle for a single.
Another fuller ball, driven straight to mid off.
Fuller again around off, Vihari again strokes it straight to the mid off fielder.
Another fullish ball, Vihari punches it straight to bowler this time.
Good length ball, angling into the batter, tucked towards the leg side.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahane blocks out.
Flatter on the body, Rahane goes back to the crease to push towards mid-wicket for a run.
Shortish one around off, blocked off his back foot by Vihari.
Jumps out of the crease to drive this fullish ball nicely but can't beat the mid off fielder.
Flatter outside off, blocked this time.
Fullish outside off, pushed to mid off this time.
Fullish one this time, pushed to covers.
Shortish one, worked towards the leg side for a run.
Fuller one this time, finds cover.
FOUR! Loopy fullish ball down the leg side, Vihari sweeps firmly towards the fine leg fence.
Shorter one, pushed towards point.
Full toss on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket for a single. 100-run stand comes up between the two. AND THAT WILL BE LUNCH.
Loopy fullish ball on middle from round the wicket, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short and shoots off just a bit off the surface, pushed off the back foot towards point for a run.
Flighted on middle and leg, blocked off the front foot by Rahane.
Flatter outside off, Rahane goes back into the crease to flick this towards mid-wicket. Takes a quick couple.
Fuller ball on off, pushed towards mid on to take a run.
FOUR! Loopy ball on middle and leg, Vihari dances down the track and makes this fuller one into a full toss. He launches this wide off mid on to get a boundary. First boundary of the second session.
Fullish ball on off and middle, Rahane looks to push this towards the leg side but the ball goes off his outside edge towards point for a run.
Good length in the channel outside off, blunts this off his back foot.
Fuller on the pads this time, flicked for a single down to backward square leg.
Stays in the crease to this good length ball and blunts it towards point.
Shortish delivery outside off, Rahane guides it through gully and point for a single.
Beaten! Goes past the hanging bat of Vihari with a superb ball going away from from Vihari. Lucky not to edge there.
Loopy ball on middle, punched straight down the ground to pick a couple. 300 up for India with that single.
Flatter, blocked towards the off side.
Fuller one on off, jumps out of the crease to push it towards cover for a run.
FOUR! Top shot. Fuller ball on off, Vihari creams his drive wide off Chase and the ball races to the fence in no time. Mid on and long off had no chance
Fuller on this time, pushed towards mid off for a run.
Another full one, pushed towards long on for a run.
Length ball on off, pushed towards the man at point.
On the pads of Rahane this time as he shuffles down the track, he flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Full again on the off pole, Rahane pushes it towards mid on.

100 up for Rahane! Tenth Test ton for him and he has compiled his innings really well after being dropped by Campbell. This one was on the pads, Rahane just pushes this towards mid-wicket and takes a single to get to his 100. The monkey is off his back now and he must be thinking to up the ante from here on. He gives a big hug to the non-striker Vihari and then lifts his bat towards the dressing room as he soaks in the applause.
Played to the point region by Vihari off the back foot.

Misfield from the fielder in the deep. Vihari flicks this full ball on his pads towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder from long on runs to his right but is sloppy in picking up the ball. He fumbles and the batters are able to complete the third easily.
On the pads, flicked firmly by Vihari but straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Shortish one on the hips, tucked away behind square leg for a couple.
SIX! That sailed over. First six of the innings! Shortish ball outside off, too high but Vihari plays this late and helps the ball sail over the third man fence.
Blocked off his front foot this time.
Full toss but can't make the full use of it. Vihari looks to push this towards the leg side but gets a leading edge and ball goes towards cover. They take a run
Wide outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Vihari looks to flick this one but misses as the ball kisses his pads and carries to the keeper. The Windies put in a desperate apppeal but to no avail.
good length one just outside the off pole, the ball hits the splice of his bat and bounces onto the pitch.
Another one just outside off, blocked out by Vihari.
Bouncer this time, around the off pole line. Vihari does well to sway away from it.
Fuller on the pads, driven towards mid on.

Beaten! Roach has done this number of times today but has failed to get the outside edge. Another one just outside off, Vihari looks to defend this but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards mid on off the back foot.
Off the toe end of the bat this one, Rahane looks to smash this full ball outside off over the mid off fielder but does not get enough of the bat on it. Two runs taken as the fielder mops it up.

NOT OUT! Umpires call and the review is retained by the West Indies. Now this looks very close and indeed it is. Clipping the top of leg pole. This one pitches on middle and leg, and nips back in with angle, Rahane misses his flick and is hit on the thigh pad. The Windies players put in a soft appeal but the umpire denies it. The hosts review as they think it is a close one. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no edge on this one. Hawk Eye comes in and shows that the ball is clipping leg. Nothing going the Windies' way here.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery
Bouncer around off! Rahane does well to sway away from this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Signs of urgency? Good length ball on off and middle, Rahane looks to slam this one over cover but mistimes it as the bat turns in his hand and the ball goes off the toe end of his bat towards cover. Holder takes a simple catch running back. Vihari runs towards Rahane to congratulate him. The commentators on air wondered if he was going off with him but that wasn't the case. A brilliant innings by him comes to an end and he is dismissed for 102. He has done well to put India in a dominating position as they lead by 397. The 135-run stand has been broken here.
Vihari guides it to third man off the back foot. No runs taken
Vihari comes down the track but misses it completely.
Fuller ball on off, punched towards long off for a run.
Fuller one wide outside off, Pant throws his bat at it finds cover.
Pant is off the mark with a nice cut shot. Short and wide outside off, Pant cuts it nicely through point and takes a quick couple. The lead is 400 now. How much more Kohli and India wants?

Edged but dropped! Short ball on the body of Pant who hops a bit to guide it over the slip cordon but can't get the direction it wants. The ball takes outside edge and goes high towards Shai Hope. He plucks his right hand in the air to catch that but can't hold on. The ball rolls behind him and the slip fielder runs to get the ball back. They take one.
Length ball on the middle and leg, tucked fine for a run.
Bumper this time, Vihari ducks under it nicely.
Good length ball around off, tapped towards point for a quick single.
Bumper on the body, Pant goes for the pull but he is not in a great position. Mistimes the shot which lobs in the air off his gloves and goes to fine leg for a single.
Fuller one outside off, Vihari comes across the off side to block.
Bouncer going down leg. Vihari ducks under it.
Fuller one on off, Pant drills it straight to mid off. No runs taken which means he wants to go for the fours and sixes.
Bouncer outside off, Pant looks to upper cut this but plays it awkwardly towards slip.
Goes for a heave over mid off this time but this flies off his outside edge towards backward point. Falls short of the fielder. Pant crosses ends.

FOUR! This time Vihari mistimes his shot. Bumper on the body, Vihari goes for the pull but top edges it high in the air towards fine leg. Hetmyer hares across to catch that but it falls shot and rolls to the fence.
Full toss on the middle pole and Vihari strikes it back at Holder who grabs it with one hand.
This has been driven superbly to the covers by Vihari.
Floated on the leg pole, he nudges it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Very wide outside off, VIhari tries to guide it to third man but misses.
Short and flatter this time by Chase, Vihari cuts it towards third man and takes a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Substitute Keemo Paul takes the catch at deep fine leg and Pant's short innings comes to an end. This one was tossed up on the leg pole, Pant gets down on one knee and looks to slog sweep it for a maximum. He does not get proper contact on it as it comes off the toe end of the bat and Keemo Paul does well as he dives forward and takes a difficult catch. India 6 down now and they are looking towards the skipper for the declaration. He says no as he wants Vihari to complete his ton maybe.
Floated wide outside off, Vihari drives this towards cover and takes a couple.

FOUR! Vihari going big now as the declaration edges closer. He uppishly plays this one towards mid-wicket by going down on one knee. The ball goes past Holder, from his left at mid-wicket and into the fence.
Full ball on middle and pads, Jadeja tucks towards mid-wicket and gets Vihari on strike.
Bumper outside off, Vihari is not going to do anything fancy with it. Ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! No century for Vihari then. And that is a very poor ball to get out to. This is shortish ball going down, Vihari looks to pull this one away but gets a faintest of touch of the gloves and the ball goes down the leg side for Hope to swallow. He does not make a mistake. Kohli declares with that wicket. Target for West Indies will be 419 runs.
Starts with a fullish ball down the leg side. There is a leg slip positioned and that's why that delivery. Brathwaite misses his flick.
Good length ball outside off, Brathwaite pushes this towards the off side.
Length ball outside off , KB goes to cut but this goes off his inside edge and goes fine down the leg side. A single taken. First run for Windies.
FOUR! Shortish ball outside off, Campbell goes back and guides this towards third man to get his first boundary.

Fuller one outside off, Campbell goes to drive but ball goes off his outside edge towards the second slip who dives to his left to stop that. He picks the ball up and has a shy at the bowler's end which hits. There is a run out appeal out of nowhere which has been taken to the TV umpire. However, Kohli was heard saying that Brathwaite's bat never went out of the crease as per Murali Kartik on air. The batsman is safe as he plonked his bat in. Risky but Kraigg survives.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped towards point for a single.
Shortish ball on the body, tapped onto the pitch by Campbell.
Shortish ball outside off, left alone by the batsman. The ball shaped in after passing the batsman.
Good length ball closer to the off stump line, pushed towards cover for a quick single.

OUT! First blood drawn! Exactly the kind of start India wanted. Good length ball outside off which shapes just a tad bit away. Brathwaite fends at it but gets an outside edge on it and the ball goes straight to Rishabh Pant behind the stumps. Brathwaite's poor run in the game continues but he would have wanted to continue here as West Indies are way behind India. The Windies lose their first wicket and they still need 412 runs.
Good length ball outside off, goes further away as Brooks lets it go.
Good length ball on off, blocked off his back foot.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, left alone again by the left-hander.
Good length ball outside off, Campbell looks to defend but is beaten as the ball shapes away.
Good length on the stumps, blocked coming forward this time.
Fullish ball closer to the stumps, blocked off his front foot.
Good length ball in the channel, pushed towards gully.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket to take a run. He is off the mark with that.
Shortish one on the body, tucked to square leg for a run.
Fullish one outside off, driven wide off cover for a quick single.
Fullish one wide outside off, left alone.

OUT! BOWLED! Knocked him over with a ripper! Fullish ball on off, Campbell is rooted to his crease as he goes for an expansive drive but misses the ball altogether as he played down the wrong line. The ball sneaks in to uproot the off stump. Windies in all sorts of trouble early on.
Good length ball down the leg side, Bravo looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.

OUT! LBW! Another one! Game over on the fourth day? Full ball on middle from Ishant, Brooks looks to flick this but misses it altogether to get hit flush on the pads. Huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger after thinking. The batters converge to discuss about taking a review but they decide against it. A good call eventually as the Ball Tracker arrives and it shows that the on-field call would've stayed as the ball was clipping the leg pole.
Good length ball outside off, shapes a bit away from the left-hander. Left alone.
Beaten the outside edge! Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer pokes at it but the ball goes away a tad bit.
Good length ball, tapped to point.
Shortish ball on the hip, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Bumper but too high as Bravo ducks under it. Pant leaps high in the air and gets his hand to it. Saves runs.
Length ball around middle and off, pushed towards mid off by Hetmyer.

Beaten! Bumrah getting some great movement here. This is pitched around middle and off, Hetmyer looks to defend but does so inside the line. The ball whizzes past the outside edge after it pitches and straightens. Oohs and aahs by the Indian players.

DROPPED! An unlikely one by the skipper here. Another one around off on a length, Hetmyer defends at this one and gets an outside edge on it. It carries straight to Kohli at third slip but he puts it down. KL Rahul tries to go for from second slip but is too late. India would have put themselves in a strong position to wrap up this match today itself had the skipper taken this.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Another one outside off, Shimron lets it through.
Outside off, left alone by Hetmyer.
Shortish ball in the channel, Bravo drops his wrists and allows the ball to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Bravo covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball outside off by Ishant, Bravo lets it be.
Length ball on the off pole, pushed back towards the bowler by Bravo.
On the pads this time by Ishant, Bravo tries to flick but misses and the ball kisses his pads. It was rolling down towards fine leg but Pant does well to dive to his right and stop it.
NO BALL! Good length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Hetmyer.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Hetmyer holes out and Rahane makes amends for the dropped catch by his skipper. Fullish ball outside off, Hetmyer looks to drive at this one but he was nowhere near it. The ball moves away after pitching, it gets the thick outside edge of Hetmyer's bat and this time Rahane at third slip makes no mistake. Hetmyer, unlike Rahane cannot make the most of the dropped chance. West Indies 4 down and their wickets are falling like ninepins.
Fuller one on the pads, Bravo goes for a flick but this goes uppishly over short backward square leg. The ball rolls fine and they take two. Off the mark with that.
Wide outside off, left alone.

OUT! BOWLED! Bumrah is on fire! Number three for him and half the Windies side is done inside 8 overs for just 15 runs. Fuller ball on off, swinging into the batsman. Bravo looks for a drive by being rooted in the crease. The ball swings in to sneak through the bat and pad to shatter the stumps. Bravo has no clue what happened as he walks back to the pavilion. AND THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Another good length ball in the channel outside off, Hope lets its be.
Good length again but shapes a bit away. Left alone by Hope again.
FOUR! Off the mark with a superb shot. Fuller ball on the pads for Chase who flicks it nicely through backward square leg for a boundary.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fullish on the fourth stump line, Chase blunts this towards the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Chase directs it through gully and point to pick up a couple. Good batting from Chase.
Bumper but too high. Chase sways away from it.
FOUR LEG BYES! Inswinging ball on the pads, Chase goes for another flick but misses to get bat on ball. It hits the pad and goes fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Good ball that but played nicely too. Came in with the angle from a good length. Hope pushes it towards mid-wicket and takes a run. He is off and running.
In the channel outside off, Chase covers his off stump and lets it be. The ball came in as it went past the stumps.
Fullish ball this time from Bumrah. Chase misses his flick and is hit flush on the pads. Appeal from slip cordon but nothing from Bumrah as he knew this was going down the leg side.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Length ball closer to the off pole, blocked off his front foot.
Fuller one to end the over. Chase lunges forward to keep it out.
Beaten! Superb ball from Ishant. Good length ball which landed on the fifth stump line and came closer to Hope. He has a poke but is beaten.
Fifth stump ball on a good length, left alone.
Good length ball on off, this time Hope blocks it off his back foot.

HUGE APPEAL FOR A CAUGHT BEHIND! Not out says that umpire. This is a peach from Ishant which pitches on a good length ball and comes in. Hope looks to work it down the leg side but is late in the shot. Pant pouches the ball behind and makes a huge appeal. He looked confident but Kohli does not go for the review. A good call from the Indian skipper as the Hawk Eye suggested that it hit the back pad of Hope and not the bat.
Good length ball is been pushed towards cover.
Sloppy fielding which allows a single. Good length ball on off, Hope pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! BOWLED! Hope is outta here! The off pole is sent cartwheeling by Bumrah again. His fourth wicket of the innings and he looks imperious with the ball in his hand right now. This was a good length ball around middle and off, it swings away after pitching. Hope tries to block it out but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement of the ball. It crashes into the off pole and the Indian players are ecstatic as the Windies are 6 down. Almost an unplayable delivery this and the visitors are just four wickets away from a victory.

Fuller outside off this time, Holder looked to drive but withdrew his decision at the last moment. Gets hit low on the bat and the ball goes towards the slip cordon. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but he is safe.
Goes past the outside edge this time. He continues to swing the ball away from the right-handers from a good length area. Holder has a poke but is beaten.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.
Length ball which comes in this time. Holder goes to flick this but is hit on the thigh pad. There is an appeal from the Indians but nothing from the umpire. This was going down the leg side.
Beaten again! Good length ball closer to off pole, Chase has a poke at it but the ball shapes away to get past the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone by Holder.
On the pads this one, flicked by Holder and this is just short of the square leg fielder. Almost carried to the fielder this one.
Another one outside off, left alone by Holder.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

DROPPED! Second drop of the innings and this time it is Holder who survives. On the hips of Jason, he flicks this one uppishly towards the square leg where Vihari was stationed. The last one fell short but this one carried to him at the perfect height to his right. Vihari gets two hands to it but it wobbles out. Ishant looks disappointed with him but captain Kohli tells him to keep his chin up.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Bumrah wants to shatter the timbers as he bowls another fullish ball which comes into the right-hander. Holder plays late and does well to block.
Another fullish ball but this is on the leg side. Holder goes for a flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters take a bye.
Another good ball. Good length, angled away this time. Left alone by Chase.
Fuller one again on a good length. Chase gets behind the line of the delivery to block towards the leg side.
Another fullish one which Bumrah wants to hit the target with. Chase is right behind the line again. Blocks well.
Fuller length again to finish the over. Blocked nicely again by Bumrah.
Flat and around off, the ball pitches and turns away sharply. Holder looks to block this one but is beaten.
Outside off this time, pushed to point.
Another one flat and on middle, pushed back towards Jadeja.
Fuller and floated, blocked out by Holder.
FOUR! This is way too short and Holder dispatches it. He rocks onto the back foot and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full and floated outside off, pushed through cover by Holder for three. He retains strike.
Length ball around middle and off, blocked out by Holder off the back foot.

OUT! 5-fer for Bumrah and the Windies skipper is out of here as well. India three wickets away from a victory here. Trademark Bumrah delivery as he bowls a yorker on the off pole, Holder plays down the wrong line as the ball shapes a tad bit away past the defense of Holder and shatters the stumps behind. Fourth fifer for the pacer in Test matches.
The ball strikes the batsman very low on the pads
Outside off, left alone by Roach.

NOT OUT! Yes! Going down. Good decision from the umpire. Bumrah bowls a beauty. This one has swung in and hit Roach on the knee roll as he misses his block. It seemed going down the leg pole and the Hawk Eye confirms the umpires decision.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short and wide outside off, Chase cuts it off the back foot and takes a couple.
On the pads, floated by Jadeja. Chase blocks it out.
This one is on the pads, Chase flicks it down to fine leg and sets off. Bumrah hares after it and stops it just inside the fence. Three runs taken by the batters.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Slammed straight down the ground by Roach. Full and floated on off, Roach gets his front leg out of the way and slams it over mid off for a boundary.
Flat and short outside off, Roach cuts it towards point.
Shami starts off with a length ball outside off, left alone by Chase.
Another length ball outside off by Shami, well left by Chase.
This time Chase blocks it out off his front foot towards cover.
Beaten! On the fifth stump line, Chase looks to defend it off the back foot but misses as he does so inside the line.
On middle and off, Chase blocks it out off his back foot.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball way outside off, it swings in sharply. Roach looks to block it out but gets a thick inside edge on it as the ball rolls towards square leg and the batters take one.
Fuller this time, Chase blocks it out well off his front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Chase pushes this towards cover and takes one.
Good length ball around the fourth stump line, Roach pushes it towards mid on.
Yorker this time by Ishant. He jams it out towards mid on.
Sharma bowls a full length ball around off, pushed to cover by Roach. He takes a single and retains strike.
Full and on the pads, Roach pushes it towards mid on and takes a single. 50 up for West Indies here.

OUT! BOWLED! The last recognized batsman for the hosts departs. Shami bowls this one around a length and off, it pitches and straightens a bit. Chase doesn't anticipate the movement and plays down the wrong line as he tries to flick it towards the leg side. The ball crashes into the off pole and Chase has to make the long walk back. The umpires have a check about the legality of the delivery. No issues with it. Shami's foot is well inside the crease. India 2 wickets away from the win.
Bouncer by Shami, way too high for Gabriel and down the leg side. Pant jumps and saves it with his left hand.
Gabriel misses his flick to this ball on the leg pole. It hits him on the pad, the ball rolls towards square leg.
The batsman has punched that ball through the offside.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another wicket for Shami and the Windies are 9 down. Length ball around the off pole, Gabriel looks to lift it over mid off but does so down the wrong line. He gets an outside edge on it and the ball carries to the keeper, Rishabh Pant. He takes the easiest of catches and the Indians rejoice. Shocking collapse this from the hosts says Mr. Gavaskar on air. India need just one wicket to seal the victory.
Good length ball down the leg side, Roach goes for a flick but misses.
SIX! Where did that come from? Back of a length ball outside off, Roach hooks that cleanly over deep mid-wicket for a six.
Good length around off, Roach blocks it towards off side.

NOT OUT! Just over middle and leg stump. Good length ball on middle and leg, Roach looks to works this towards the leg side but is hit high on the pads. The Indians make a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Chase opts for a review and it is a good one as Ball Tracker shows that this is going just over the stumps.
Blocked this fuller ball nicely.
Goes for a almighty heave but is beaten by the pace of the delivery.
Good length ball but going down the leg side. Cummins goes for a flick but misses. Pant does well to pouch that one.
Bouncer this time. Cummins ducks under it.
Good length ball in the outside off channel, Cummins blunts this one nicely towards the off side.
Another solid block from Cummins by getting right behind the line of this good length ball.
Beaten this time. Shami lands this one on a good length area, the ball shapes away and goes past the drive of Cummins.
Fullish length outside off, left alone.
SIX! Slammed straight over the head of Jadeja by Roach! Floated full and on middle, Roach just slams it straight as an arrow into the sight screen for a biggie.
SIX! Back-to-back sixes for Holder. Flighted ball outside off, Roach slams this powerfully over the long fence for another maximum.
This time he blocks this flatter one.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
SIX! Floated on middle and leg, Roach gives this the treatment as he slogs it over mid-wicket for a maximum. Third six from the over. Roach moves to 31 in a jiffy.
Looks to defend this time but the ball turns away and goes past the outside edge.
Short ball but too high. Cummins ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off this time, left alone.
Good length ball from round the wicket, this comes into the left-hander. Blocked nicely by Cummins.
Goes for a yorker this time but dishes a low full toss. Cummins does well to push towards covers.
Bumper now! Cummins ducks under it.
Shami goes past the outside edge as Cummins goes for the drive off this good length ball outside off.
Flatter one on middle, blocked by Roach.
Flatter on middle again, Roach slams this flat over the bowler's head. Gets a single as Vihari from long on gets to the ball.
Fuller ball around off, Cummins goes for a drive but gets an under edge. The ball goes through the legs of Pant and to the third man fence. First runs after 57 balls for him.
Fuller one on middle, pushed back towards mid off.
Fuller on middle, blocked nicely.
Floated on middle and leg, Cummins plays this uppishly towards mid-wicket but gets it past him as the batters take three.

Hit on the helmet! But he says he is fine. KL Rahul and Rahane come instantly towards Cummins to check with him. This was not a shortish one to be ducked under but Cummins ducks and gets hit on the head gear. Jadeja also checks with Cummins whether he is fine.
FOUR! Good length ball on off, Cummins crunches this through mid off for a boundary.
SIX! Slammed over the long on fence for a six now. Good length ball on off, Cummins clears his front leg and slogs this one over the long on fence. Some blow that from Cummins. Frustration for India.
Bumper outside off, ducked by Cummins.
Goes for a slower and fuller ball this time. Cummins reads it well to block.
Length delivery outside off, Cummins this time cuts through covers and takes two. Expensive over this.
Goes for a slower yorker. Roach works it through mid-wicket. Doesn't take a run.
Goes for a heave to this good length ball on off but mistimes it towards mid on.

SIX! Another one hammered for a maximum. Some hitting this from Roach. 100 up with that and a 50-run stand as well. Fullish ball on middle and leg, Roach clears his front leg again and lofts this over the mid on fielder.
Shortish one outside off, Roach goes for an almighty heave but misses it altogether.

OUT! CAUGHT! Top Edge and taken. Back of a length ball again as Roach goes for a pull. He slices this high in the air. Pant hares to his left to gobble this one nicely. INDIA TAKE THE FIRST GAME OF THE SERIES AS THEY WIN BY 318 RUNS.
